      • checkExtRefInfoCoherence

        public TExtRef checkExtRefInfoCoherence​(@NonNull
                                        @NonNull ExtRefInfo extRefInfo)
                                 throws ScdException
        Verify the coherence of ExtRef info. This method look up the TExtRef that matches the signal info in this LNode. Then verify the coherence between the ExtRef's binding info and the given binding info. If the ExtRef info contains a source information ( ControlBlock info),it verifies that the CB and dataset it points to, exists within and existing binder IED.
        Parameters:
        extRefInfo - ExtRef information (signal, binding and source info)
        Returns:
        TExtRef that matches the signal info
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - when no given signal info
        ScdException - throws exception if
        • given signal info or it doesn't match any TExtRef in this LNode
        • the given binding info doesn't match the found TExtRef's binding info.
        • the given binding info doesn't refer to an exiting IED, LDevice and LNode in the SCL
        • given source info references unknown control block

      • getDAI

        public List<ResumedDataTemplate> getDAI​(ResumedDataTemplate rDtt,
                                        boolean updatableOnly)
                                 throws ScdException
        Returns a list of resumed DataTypeTemplate for DataAttribute (updatable or not)
        Parameters:
        rDtt - reference resumed DataTypeTemplate (used as filter)
        updatableOnly - true to retrieve only updatable DAI, false to retrieve all DAI
        Returns:
        List of resumed DataTypeTemplate for DataAttribute (updatable or not)
        Throws:
        ScdException - SCD illegal arguments exception

      • findMatch

        protected Optional<IDataAdapter> findMatch​(DoTypeName doTypeName,
                                           DaTypeName daTypeName)
        Search for DAI that match the given defined-DO (do.sdo1[.sdo2 ...sdo_n]) and defined-DA (da.bda1[.bda2...bda_n]) where 'sdo_n' points to a DOType that contains 'da'
        Parameters:

        daTypeName - defined-DA (da.bda1[.bda2...bda_n])
        Returns:
        Optional of DAIAdapter for the matched DAI
